text:
Hi Lucy, It's going ok 
I have an interview for UAL camberwell coming up soon and my portfolio is near completion now

I decided to not include the character sheets in the end as per your suggestion last time, since my teacher told me not to put in anything I'm not proud of. 
If you could take a look at what I've put together that would be helpful :) since both my art teachers are off sick. I know it's been a while since we last spoke so I hope you're doing ok too. Sorry for not checking in as much as I should have
Hello Jane. Of course. It's definitely good advice not to include anything you're not proud of - even if I think it's good. :slightly_smiling_face:

Im glad you think it's good, tend to think that everything I make is sub par but I'm working on breaking that mindset. 
If you could give me 5 minutes, I can send you better quality photos of my portfolio (since it's a physical one and I need to get the sheets laid out)

the lighting isn't very good on some of the sheets, sorry about that :( 
But I've sent it in order of how I will present it

(For the first slide, I plan to give the interviewer a copy of the physical book with chapter 1 inside to flick through briefly, I plan to change the orientation of the second slide to vertical to match the rest here too)
I made the room page notes neater here too, I sent the digital version here if you're interested in reading it and taking a closer look
(The pages that have the photographs of the final sculpture still need to be printed since the school printer is being replace currently)

I'm not sure whether to include the final sweet drawing here at the end, but everything else I added certain (for now), I'm not expecting feedback straight away since my interview is on the 18th I don't want to rush you or anything
Hello Jane. I'm going to get one of my artists to look through this stuff with me and then give you some feedback :slightly_smiling_face:
